  "slug": "valid-sudoku",
  "title": "Valid Sudoku",
  "difficulty": "Medium",
  "tags": [
    "Array",
    "Hash Table",
    "Matrix"
  ],
  "companies": [],
  "statement": "# Valid Sudoku\n\nGiven a partially filled 9 x 9 Sudoku board, return whether every filled cell obeys the Sudoku rules. Empty cells are represented by `.`. The board does not need to be solvable.\n\n## Examples\n\n**Example 1**\n\n```text\nInput: board = partially filled board with no repeated row, column, or box values\nOutput: true\n```\n\n**Example 2**\n\n```text\nInput: board = same board but row 0 contains two 5 values\nOutput: false\n```\n\n**Example 3**\n\n```text\nInput: board = same board but column 0 contains two 6 values\nOutput: false\n```\n\n## Constraints\n\n- `board.length == 9`\n- `board[i].length == 9`\n- Each cell is `.` or a digit from `1` through `9`.",
  "editorial": "Track every filled value in three scopes: row, column, and 3 x 3 box. If any scope sees the same digit twice, the board is invalid.",
  "solution_notes": "```python\nclass Solution:\n    def isValidSudoku(self, board):\n        seen = set()\n        for r in range(9):\n            for c in range(9):\n                value = board[r][c]\n                if value == '.':\n                    continue\n                row = ('row', r, value)\n                col = ('col', c, value)\n                box = ('box', r // 3, c // 3, value)\n                if row in seen or col in seen or box in seen:\n                    return False\n                seen.update([row, col, box])\n        return True\n```",
  "hints": [
    "Check rows, columns, and boxes independently.",
    "A set can store a scoped marker such as `(row, index, digit)`."
  ],
  "starter_code": {
    "python": "class Solution:\n    def isValidSudoku(self, board):\n        pass\n"
  },
  "entrypoint": {
    "class_name": "Solution",
    "method_name": "isValidSudoku"
  },
